By John Shiklam in Kaduna Senator Shehu Sani representing Kaduna Central Senatorial zone, has finally dumped the All Progressives Congress (APC) following a failed attempt to get the party’s ticket for re-election in 2019. The automatic ticket initially given to him by the National Working Committee (NWC) of the APC was trailed by controversy. Primary election was later conducted and Uba Sani, Governor Nasir el-Rufai’s candidate for the senatorial zone, emerged winner. Sani had boycotted the primaries, describing it as “Kangaroo election” and had directed his supporters not to participate in it. Details shortly….